@node "Functions" "Functions"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Installation"

@{fg shine}Functions@{fg text}

Key ring functions                        Calls

Generate key                              -kg
Check certifying signature                -kc
Edit key                                  -ke
View contents                             -kvv
View fingerprint                          -kvc
Save ASCII key                            -kxa
Save key                                  -kx
Add key                                   -ka
Remove key                                -kr
Sign key                                  -ks
Remove signature                          -krs
Revoke key                                -kd

File functions                            Calls

Encrypt file                              -e 
Decrypt file / Check signature   
Sign file                                 -s

Settings                                  Calls

Detached signature                        +armor=on
Radix-64 Format                           -b
Signed message (Encapsuled as Clear Text) +clearsig=on

To understand exactly what You are doing, please read the PGP manual carefully.
I don't answer questions about PGP!

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Configuration"
@prev "Functions"

@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

There are only a few words to say:

The 12 button in the upper part of the main window are used for key generation
and key (ring) manipulations. Please read the dokumentation of PGP(tm) for
further information.
The next 3 buttons are use for crypting / decrypting of files.
The 3 buttons in the lower part of the main window are used for how to
operate with crypting. Read the dokumentation of PGP(tm) for further
information.

The program can be startet from the CLI or by icon. If You want the 
mainwindow to appear on a PubScreen of Your choise, You have to start the 
programm with the parameter PUBSCREEN=PubScreenName or edit the tooltype to
PUBSCREEN=PubScreenName.

The output window of PGP(tm) will be closed when finishing the program or if You
iconify the program.

@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Configuration"
@next "Shareware"
@prev "Usage"

@{fg shine}Configuration@{fg text}

To go to the settings window use menu item PREFS in the Project menu.



PGP Programm    : Edit path and program name of PGP. Do it by hand or
                  use the filerequester.

Save files to   : Edit the path name where PGP shall store files.

Get files from  : Edit the path name where You want to get files from.
                  The filerequester always opens this directory for default.

Output          : PGP(tm) writes his text's here. Normaly You will use "CON:"
                  or "KCON:" here. For default this is set to
                  "CON:////FensterTitel/SCREEN %s". "%s" will be replaced by
                  the PubScreen name if You start the program with the parameter
                  PUBSCREEN=PubScreenName from CLI or start the program by icon
                  with the tooltype PUBSCREEN=PubScreenName.

@endnode

